      }
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Preloading"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "value": "Preloading is used for critical resources needed for the current page. It tells the browser to load these resources early."
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "html",
      "value": "<link rel=\"preload\" href=\"style.css\" as=\"style\">\n<link rel=\"preload\" href=\"font.woff2\" as=\"font\" type=\"font/woff2\" crossorigin>"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Prefetching"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "value": "Prefetching is used for resources that might be needed in the future, such as next pages or assets."
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "html",
      "value": "<link rel=\"prefetch\" href=\"next-page.html\">"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "When to Use Preload"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "value": [
